WEBVTT

00:02.874 --> 00:05.374
Thank you very much.
Thanks.

00:05.376 --> 00:06.476
LEONARD:
That is unbelievable.

00:06.478 --> 00:07.710
Good for Bert.

00:07.712 --> 00:10.213
Damn, the MacArthur
Genius Grant.

00:10.215 --> 00:11.714
Couldn't have happened
to a nicer guy.

00:11.716 --> 00:14.484
Everything is stupid
and I want to go home.

00:15.487 --> 00:17.386
That's Sheldon's way of saying

00:17.388 --> 00:18.621
he's proud of Bert, too.

00:18.623 --> 00:19.889
Ah.

00:19.891 --> 00:21.824
Hey, it's not even called
the "Genius Grant,"

00:21.826 --> 00:23.626
it's the MacArthur Fellowship.

00:23.628 --> 00:25.761
Just like it's
not Frankenstein,

00:25.763 --> 00:26.963
it's "Frankenstein's Monster."

00:26.965 --> 00:27.930
Which brings us back

00:27.932 --> 00:29.932
to that hulking
simpleton over there.

00:31.803 --> 00:33.069
And if anyone's a genius,

00:33.071 --> 00:34.937
it's me for the way
I brought that full circle.

00:36.875 --> 00:38.107
How much money did he win?

00:38.109 --> 00:39.342
Over half a million dollars.

00:39.344 --> 00:40.843
- Wow.
- And he doesn't have to use it

00:40.845 --> 00:43.146
for research, he can do
whatever he wants with it.

00:43.148 --> 00:46.649
Oh, good, maybe he can build
a nicer bridge to live under.

00:47.585 --> 00:49.152
Here he comes.
Right.

00:49.154 --> 00:50.119
Be polite.

00:50.121 --> 00:51.320
I know how to behave.

00:51.322 --> 00:52.588
Do you?

00:52.590 --> 00:54.590
Hey,
congratulations Bert!

00:54.592 --> 00:55.791
Yeah, good for you.
That's amazing.

00:55.793 --> 00:56.759
Thanks.

00:56.761 --> 00:58.794
I was as surprised as anybody.

00:58.796 --> 00:59.795
When they called
and told me

00:59.797 --> 01:01.264
I won, I didn't believe them.

01:01.266 --> 01:03.399
And then they said,
"No, you really won."

01:03.401 --> 01:06.335
And then I said, "Cool."

01:06.337 --> 01:08.838
Someone call
George R. R. Martin,

01:08.840 --> 01:11.140
this guy knows how
to finish a story.

01:11.142 --> 01:14.377
I've gotten pretty good
at telling it.

01:15.580 --> 01:17.013
Well, see ya.

01:18.082 --> 01:19.448
Some genius.

01:19.450 --> 01:22.385
I zinged him with sarcasm,
he didn't even notice.

01:23.254 --> 01:24.487
I know, and it was

01:24.489 --> 01:26.656
the greatest sarcastic
quip I've ever heard.

01:26.658 --> 01:29.859
Well, aren't you a peach.

01:29.861 --> 01:33.496
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

01:33.498 --> 01:36.832
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

01:36.834 --> 01:38.467
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

01:38.469 --> 01:41.003
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

01:41.005 --> 01:43.673
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

01:43.675 --> 01:46.342
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

01:46.344 --> 01:48.244
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

01:48.246 --> 01:49.713
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

