02:00.749 --> 02:02.649
Who leaves their bike
in the hallway?

02:02.651 --> 02:03.984
You know,
if I knew how to ride one,

02:03.986 --> 02:05.218
I'd steal it.

02:06.088 --> 02:07.621
Ignore him,

02:07.623 --> 02:10.156
he's just cranky because Bert
from the geology lab

02:10.157 --> 02:11.157
won a big grant.

02:11.159 --> 02:13.293
Oh, I heard him
interviewed on the radio!

02:13.295 --> 02:14.694
You know, when they
told him he won,

02:14.696 --> 02:16.730
he didn't believe it,
but then he did believe it.

02:16.732 --> 02:18.331
It was so funny.

02:19.701 --> 02:22.002
SHELDON: Who listens
to the radio anymore?

02:23.805 --> 02:25.739
Bert is studying the way
microbes in rocks

02:25.741 --> 02:28.041
can survive in extreme
environmental conditions.

02:28.043 --> 02:29.709
They say it could be
a potential indicator

02:29.711 --> 02:31.011
of life on other planets.

02:31.013 --> 02:32.212
You know what, I've met Bert.

02:32.214 --> 02:35.649
Isn't he an indicator
of life on other planets?

02:35.651 --> 02:37.117
(chuckles)

02:37.119 --> 02:39.286
SHELDON: You used to
make those jokes about me.

02:40.455 --> 02:42.722
Now everything is
Bert, Bert, Bert!

02:44.126 --> 02:45.325
You know, Sheldon,

02:45.327 --> 02:46.393
maybe if you take the time

02:46.395 --> 02:47.727
to actually
read Bert's research,

02:47.729 --> 02:49.296
you'd be less bitter
about him winning.

02:49.298 --> 02:51.031
(stammering):
You want me to read

02:51.033 --> 02:52.732
a geology paper?

02:52.734 --> 02:54.200
Honestly, I just
want you to be quiet

02:54.202 --> 02:55.535
but I'm all out of taffy.

02:58.974 --> 03:00.707
(knocking)
You busy?

03:00.709 --> 03:02.876
There's somebody out here
who wants to meet you.

03:02.878 --> 03:04.110
Who is it?

03:04.112 --> 03:06.613
Say hello to everybody's
little friend--

03:06.615 --> 03:08.948
remote control
Stephen Hawking!

03:13.722 --> 03:15.488
Where did you get that?

03:15.490 --> 03:17.324
I found him in an old box.

03:17.326 --> 03:19.759
Why would you buy it?

03:19.761 --> 03:21.594
I didn't buy it.

03:21.596 --> 03:23.463
I made it.

03:24.333 --> 03:25.432
Last question.

03:25.434 --> 03:27.701
What is wrong with you?

03:28.603 --> 03:30.570
What's the big deal?

03:30.572 --> 03:32.372
Howie, it's in poor taste.

03:32.374 --> 03:33.773
No, it's not.
Check it out.

03:33.775 --> 03:35.041
He says fun stuff.

03:35.043 --> 03:37.010
RC HAWKING:
Hey good lookin',

03:37.012 --> 03:39.012
want to go for a spin?

03:44.653 --> 03:48.088
His eyes also light up
in the dark.

03:53.995 --> 03:57.097
It's always fun watching him
read someone else's work.

03:57.966 --> 03:59.566
(scoffs)

04:03.872 --> 04:05.739
(moans)

04:11.313 --> 04:13.847
It's like scrolling
through the emojis

04:13.849 --> 04:16.182
on my phone.

04:17.017 --> 04:19.219
Ye-- why?

04:20.988 --> 04:22.989
Eh, why?!

04:24.893 --> 04:27.026
Oh, that's why.

04:27.028 --> 04:29.562
Sounds like the night
we had coitus.

04:32.167 --> 04:34.300
I hope you're happy
making me read this.

04:34.302 --> 04:35.902
Bert's work is remarkable.

04:35.904 --> 04:37.270
And I'm more upset
than ever.

04:37.272 --> 04:38.838
This is worse than
when I had to admit that

04:38.840 --> 04:41.841
Cedric the Entertainer's
actually entertaining.

04:41.843 --> 04:43.977
Sheldon, it's foolish

04:43.979 --> 04:46.413
to be angry that
Bert's work has merit.

04:46.415 --> 04:48.381
Yeah, well I-I am angry!

04:48.383 --> 04:49.883
And you telling me
not to be angry

04:49.885 --> 04:50.850
makes me angry!

04:50.852 --> 04:52.152
And do you know how
hearing myself

04:52.154 --> 04:54.187
say the word angry
over and over makes me feel?

04:54.189 --> 04:56.189
Ooh, a-angry?
What are you doing?

04:57.826 --> 05:00.493
I-I-I knew the answer.
I got excited.

05:01.863 --> 05:03.396
Hey, buddy, why don't
we go for a walk,

05:03.398 --> 05:04.531
so you can calm down.

05:04.533 --> 05:05.598
(sighs)

05:05.600 --> 05:06.766
That's a good idea.

05:06.768 --> 05:08.868
I guess everyone's
having them now.

05:09.704 --> 05:11.638
Hey, I'm trying
to help you.

05:11.640 --> 05:12.806
Fine.

05:12.808 --> 05:15.041
You can walk ahead of me
and scare off the pigeons.

05:18.413 --> 05:21.714
Just wave your arms a little
and they fly away, it's not...

05:24.319 --> 05:25.752
Okay, Raj,

05:25.754 --> 05:27.387
I'm gonna
show you something.

05:27.389 --> 05:28.421
Now,

05:28.423 --> 05:31.090
one of us thinks it's offensive.

05:31.092 --> 05:33.393
The other thinks it's hilarious

05:33.395 --> 05:35.628
and a great idea.

05:36.531 --> 05:38.465
But, I'm not
going to tell you

05:38.467 --> 05:39.899
who likes it.

05:47.542 --> 05:49.742
This is tough.

05:51.313 --> 05:52.846
But I'm going to say

05:52.848 --> 05:54.714
it's the guy who
shows me YouTube videos

05:54.716 --> 05:57.550
of people getting hit
in the nuts.

05:57.552 --> 05:59.285
(laughing)

05:59.287 --> 06:00.787
You're crazy.

06:00.789 --> 06:01.921
I've worked with Hawking.

06:01.923 --> 06:03.256
He's got a great sense of humor.

06:03.258 --> 06:04.224
And I think he'd like it.

06:04.226 --> 06:06.226
Okay, call him and show him.

06:06.228 --> 06:07.694
I dare you.

06:07.696 --> 06:09.929
I have no problem calling him.

06:09.931 --> 06:11.197
Fine, then do it.

06:11.199 --> 06:12.732
Fine, I will.

06:14.369 --> 06:18.037
While you're bothering the
world's most famous scientist,

06:18.039 --> 06:19.639
be sure to show him
how funny he looks

06:19.641 --> 06:21.841
getting stuck
under our dishwasher.

06:23.578 --> 06:25.078
What's this button do?

06:25.080 --> 06:28.481
Gentlemen,
start your wheelchairs.

06:31.620 --> 06:34.587
You laughed when that guy
got hit in the nuts.

06:37.259 --> 06:40.226
I laughed because
the guy was Leonard.

06:42.998 --> 06:45.765
I admire you, Leonard.

06:45.767 --> 06:48.067
Really, why?

06:48.069 --> 06:50.136
You're happy with who you are.

06:50.138 --> 06:52.672
You don't get jealous
of other people.

06:52.674 --> 06:55.608
Instead of being
weighed down by ambition,

06:55.610 --> 06:59.212
you just float along
like a dead body in a river.

07:02.083 --> 07:03.283
I couldn't just
take the compliment.

07:03.285 --> 07:04.617
I had to ask why.

07:07.822 --> 07:10.523
You know, I do understand
what you're feeling.

07:10.525 --> 07:12.458
My brother and sister's
accomplishments

07:12.460 --> 07:14.360
have always been
held over my head.

07:15.297 --> 07:16.729
How did you deal with it?

07:16.731 --> 07:19.332
I wet the bed until college,
but I don't think

07:19.334 --> 07:21.401
that's a quality fix.

07:22.237 --> 07:23.436
(groans)

07:23.438 --> 07:27.040
I can't believe I was
surpassed by a geologist.

07:27.042 --> 07:29.409
I mean...

07:29.411 --> 07:30.610
rocks!

07:30.612 --> 07:32.845
He studies rocks!

07:32.847 --> 07:35.848
If rock is so great,
how come paper beats it?

07:39.154 --> 07:40.553
Leonard, I'm having
a primal urge

07:40.555 --> 07:42.288
to throw this rock.

07:42.290 --> 07:43.323
Do it.

07:43.325 --> 07:45.191
Visualize it
as your anger

07:45.193 --> 07:47.393
a-and-and toss it
out of your life.

07:49.264 --> 07:51.464
Perhaps I will.

07:54.669 --> 07:56.436
This rock

07:56.438 --> 07:59.405
encapsulates
all my negative emotions.

08:00.208 --> 08:03.576
I will cast you far away.

08:03.578 --> 08:06.112
Feel free to take out a pigeon
while you're at it.

08:07.616 --> 08:09.749
Let it fly.

08:10.585 --> 08:11.651
(inhales deeply)

08:11.653 --> 08:13.853
Ow, ow, ow, ow,

08:13.855 --> 08:16.356
ow, ow, ow, ow...

08:17.525 --> 08:19.192
What happened?

08:19.194 --> 08:20.893
I tried to let go of anger

08:20.895 --> 08:23.429
and threw a rock
into my foot!

08:24.399 --> 08:26.532
Then he got more angry
and kicked the rock

08:26.534 --> 08:28.201
with his other foot.
Wha--?

08:28.203 --> 08:29.802
And what happened to you?

08:29.804 --> 08:31.104
Oh, I laughed so hard,

08:31.106 --> 08:32.871
I burst a blood vessel
in my nose. It's fine.

08:34.000 --> 08:40.073
