08:43.159 --> 08:45.260
You know, it's one thing
to be envious,

08:45.262 --> 08:46.795
but now you're
injuring yourself.

08:46.797 --> 08:48.697
It has to stop.

08:48.699 --> 08:49.932
Although if you are
gonna do it again,

08:49.934 --> 08:53.001
please let me know,
so I can get it on video.

08:53.003 --> 08:54.536
You know, Sheldon,

08:54.538 --> 08:57.106
instead of fixating
on what Bert has,

08:57.108 --> 08:58.073
you should appreciate

08:58.075 --> 09:00.042
all of the good things
in your life.

09:00.044 --> 09:01.543
Y-You've got love,

09:01.545 --> 09:02.811
you're in good health,

09:02.813 --> 09:04.213
you've got a roof
over your head.

09:04.215 --> 09:05.381
Yeah,

09:05.383 --> 09:07.182
but you've got all those things,

09:07.184 --> 09:09.184
and no one's lining up
to be you.

09:11.589 --> 09:12.821
Anybody else want to try?

09:12.823 --> 09:13.889
I'm gonna go
make some more tea

09:13.891 --> 09:15.257
and question
my life choices.

09:17.027 --> 09:18.060
LEONARD:
You're up.

09:18.062 --> 09:19.495
(Penny clears throat)

09:19.497 --> 09:23.232
This is getting old fast,
Dolores, knock it off!

09:24.101 --> 09:25.601
Uh, do you really think

09:25.603 --> 09:26.702
calling me names is helpful?

09:26.704 --> 09:27.636
I do!

09:27.638 --> 09:29.872
Your life is fine,
you big baby!

09:29.874 --> 09:31.407
Maybe you're right.

09:31.409 --> 09:32.775
Really?!

09:34.011 --> 09:35.811
If it helps,
I'm questioning

09:35.813 --> 09:38.013
your life choices, too.

09:38.015 --> 09:39.314
Thank you, Penny.

09:39.316 --> 09:40.983
You know, I just need
to keep reminding myself

09:40.985 --> 09:43.619
that Bert's success
is not my failure.

09:43.621 --> 09:44.686
There you go.

09:44.688 --> 09:46.021
And that men
of his large stature

09:46.023 --> 09:47.689
are more susceptible
to a wide array

09:47.691 --> 09:50.392
of life-threatening diseases.

09:50.394 --> 09:52.461
There you go...

09:57.802 --> 09:59.334
What's up?

09:59.336 --> 10:01.069
I'm conducting
a quick survey.

10:01.071 --> 10:03.305
Do you think this
respectful

10:03.307 --> 10:06.642
and loving tribute
to a great man

10:06.644 --> 10:08.677
is in poor taste?

10:16.687 --> 10:18.620
Yep.

10:20.758 --> 10:23.292
Do you think this is
in poor taste?

10:23.294 --> 10:25.027
Does it spin around
and do tricks?

10:25.029 --> 10:25.928
Yeah!

10:25.930 --> 10:27.062
Then yeah.

10:28.098 --> 10:29.331
What do you think?

10:29.333 --> 10:32.701
That is hilarious!

10:34.038 --> 10:35.304
Give me the remote control.

10:35.306 --> 10:37.272
I want to drive him
into the girls' restroom.

10:38.642 --> 10:40.876
All right, we're done.
It's offensive.

10:51.388 --> 10:53.689
Top of the afternoon,
gentlemen.

10:53.691 --> 10:54.957
You're in a good mood.

10:54.959 --> 10:57.659
Well, it's a new day.
I have a new outlook.

10:57.661 --> 10:59.795
You know, I realized
I don't need to worry

10:59.797 --> 11:01.063
about other people.

11:01.065 --> 11:04.533
I just need to think
more about myself.

11:07.071 --> 11:11.006
Oh, how will we ever
get used to the new you?

11:11.942 --> 11:14.243
Well, I'm glad to
see you moving forward.

11:14.245 --> 11:15.911
Bert did quality
research.

11:15.913 --> 11:19.114
And he deserves whatever
accolades he receives.

11:19.116 --> 11:20.983
What is going on?

11:20.985 --> 11:23.385
Did you upgrade
his software last night?

11:24.421 --> 11:26.255
I think he might be
learning on his own.

11:26.257 --> 11:29.091
Then the robot uprising
has begun.

11:30.528 --> 11:32.461
Excuse me, I need to pay Bert

11:32.463 --> 11:35.297
a proper congratulations.

11:37.868 --> 11:39.935
He doesn't just look
like C-3PO,

11:39.937 --> 11:41.603
now he walks like him.

11:42.873 --> 11:44.039
Bert?

11:44.041 --> 11:47.175
I wanted to let you know
that I read your research,

11:47.177 --> 11:50.178
and your award is
well-deserved.

11:50.180 --> 11:53.282
Thanks. I've been
hearing that a lot.

11:53.284 --> 11:56.418
Ever since I won,
people think I'm great.

11:56.420 --> 11:58.921
Well, just this once,

11:58.923 --> 12:01.723
you can count me as people, too.

12:03.961 --> 12:06.595
You know, as a
MacArthur Grant winner,

12:06.597 --> 12:08.931
I'm allowed to nominate
someone for next year.

12:08.933 --> 12:11.667
Really?

12:11.669 --> 12:13.569
I didn't know that.

12:13.571 --> 12:14.770
So I was thinking,
you know,

12:14.772 --> 12:16.305
engineers don't get
a lot of respect.

12:16.307 --> 12:19.975
Is your friend Howard
working on anything cool?

12:22.546 --> 12:24.179
You know, I-I'm not sure.

12:24.181 --> 12:26.348
You know, you'd have to ask him.

12:26.350 --> 12:27.549
Excuse me.

12:35.426 --> 12:36.892
Aah!
(loud bang, thud)

12:39.063 --> 12:42.731
SHELDON: Leonard!
I hurt myself again.

12:44.401 --> 12:47.970
Excuse me, I-I have to
go take some pictures.

12:50.140 --> 12:52.841
I can't believe you
head-butted a water fountain.

12:54.278 --> 12:58.246
No, I went to punch
the water fountain,

12:58.248 --> 13:00.449
slipped in water in front
of the water fountain,

13:00.451 --> 13:03.552
and hit my head
on the water fountain.

13:03.554 --> 13:06.388
I can't imagine you
being violent.

13:06.390 --> 13:08.590
It's not hard.
Just picture the Three Stooges,

13:08.592 --> 13:10.859
and then take away two stooges.

13:11.996 --> 13:14.396
I'm so disappointed
in myself.

13:14.398 --> 13:16.965
Jealousy is
completely illogical.

13:16.967 --> 13:18.533
It's a human
emotion, Sheldon.

13:18.535 --> 13:19.901
Everyone gets jealous.

13:19.903 --> 13:21.603
I'm jealous of
Leonard and Penny

13:21.605 --> 13:22.638
and Howard and Bernadette

13:22.640 --> 13:24.406
for being in such
happy relationships.

13:24.408 --> 13:27.275
What about me and Sheldon?

13:29.246 --> 13:30.445
Sure.

13:33.951 --> 13:35.984
I've always been jealous
of how much money

13:35.986 --> 13:37.786
Raj's family has.

13:37.788 --> 13:39.521
Thank you for saying that.
Next to buying things,

13:39.523 --> 13:42.491
that is the best part
about having money.

13:42.493 --> 13:44.326
Ever since I met Penny,

13:44.328 --> 13:46.328
I've been envious
of her looks.

13:46.330 --> 13:48.530
Aw, thank you.

13:48.532 --> 13:50.365
That's why I was so happy
when you cut your hair off.

13:50.367 --> 13:51.433
What?!

13:51.435 --> 13:53.068
You know what I mean.

13:53.070 --> 13:54.636
You were still hot,
but more like a

13:54.638 --> 13:57.339
"why'd that hot girl
cut off all her hair?" hot.

13:58.542 --> 14:00.108
You liked my
short hair, right?

14:00.110 --> 14:02.911
Yeah... I loved it.

14:02.913 --> 14:06.248
Love you, love the hair, would
love to change the subject.

14:07.918 --> 14:10.752
Seriously, none of you liked it?

14:11.689 --> 14:13.255
I thought it was brave.

14:13.257 --> 14:15.857
Does that count as liking it?

14:17.227 --> 14:18.827
You know, how come
nobody's talking about

14:18.829 --> 14:20.996
Howard's dopey haircut?

14:24.001 --> 14:25.534
I think he looks cute.

14:25.536 --> 14:26.668
And I think
you're cute.

14:26.670 --> 14:27.803
I think you're both cute.

14:27.805 --> 14:30.238
I think I hate all of you nerds.

14:36.613 --> 14:38.246
Sorry I'm moving slowly.

14:38.248 --> 14:39.381
Oh, I don't mind.

14:39.383 --> 14:41.416
If you pull a butterscotch
out of your pocket,

14:41.418 --> 14:44.386
it would be like I'm
walking with my grandma.

14:46.623 --> 14:48.457
Oh, no.

14:52.563 --> 14:55.397
Did you...
A plaque?

14:55.399 --> 14:57.966
Nobody wants to see this.

14:57.968 --> 15:00.535
Well, change "plaque"
to "mixed-race couple"

15:00.537 --> 15:03.071
and you are my grandma.

15:03.073 --> 15:05.640
I can't take this anymore.

15:07.244 --> 15:10.312
Bert. Bert.
Bert!

15:10.314 --> 15:11.546
BERT:
Come in.

15:11.548 --> 15:14.082
All right, let's do this...

15:18.422 --> 15:19.955
Bert?

15:19.957 --> 15:21.323
We need to talk.

15:21.325 --> 15:22.524
What happened to you?

15:22.526 --> 15:25.160
Rock, rock, water fountain.

15:27.798 --> 15:29.197
I am not proud of this.

15:29.199 --> 15:32.267
But I have been envious
of your recent success.

15:32.269 --> 15:35.804
Wow, I won the MacArthur Grant,

15:35.806 --> 15:37.239
everyone's jealous of me.

15:37.241 --> 15:40.776
Once I get Lasik, I'll be
out of things to wish for.

15:41.879 --> 15:44.079
I was hoping by admitting
my weakness to you,

15:44.081 --> 15:45.981
I'd somehow be unburdened.

15:45.983 --> 15:47.249
Is it working?
No.

15:47.251 --> 15:48.316
Now that you know my weakness,

15:48.318 --> 15:49.618
I hate you more than ever.

15:51.555 --> 15:54.322
Well, you know, we're
both pretty smart.

15:54.324 --> 15:55.857
I bet if we put
our heads together,

15:55.859 --> 15:57.492
we could come up
with a solution.

15:57.494 --> 15:59.394
We... Hang on.

15:59.396 --> 16:01.730
You're my enemy.

16:01.732 --> 16:04.332
Now, the enemy of the enemy
is my friend.

16:04.334 --> 16:06.701
And right now,
I'm my own worst enemy.

16:06.703 --> 16:08.804
That makes you my fr--
Okay, I'm good to go.

16:10.307 --> 16:11.540
Great.

16:11.542 --> 16:12.941
Now that we're friends,
want to see if we can

16:12.943 --> 16:15.477
get tickets
to a taping of <i>Ellen?</i>

16:18.148 --> 16:19.781
You know what?
This isn't gonna work.

16:19.783 --> 16:23.385
Sheldon... wait.

16:23.387 --> 16:26.588
You know, you've got
a lot to be happy about.

16:26.590 --> 16:28.590
You're at the top
of your field,

16:28.592 --> 16:30.492
you have a great girlfriend.

16:30.494 --> 16:32.260
Yes! That's right!

16:32.262 --> 16:34.229
I have Amy!

16:37.367 --> 16:40.302
In the past, you've
professed feelings for her.

16:40.304 --> 16:41.770
Does it eat you up inside

16:41.772 --> 16:42.804
that I have her
and you don't?

16:42.806 --> 16:45.407
It used to.

16:45.409 --> 16:47.209
But now that I'm rich
and successful,

16:47.211 --> 16:49.311
I think I can do better.

16:51.515 --> 16:53.849
I can't believe
you punched Bert.

16:55.552 --> 16:57.252
I didn't punch him.

16:57.254 --> 16:58.987
He turned around,
and I gave him

16:58.989 --> 17:01.189
a Captain Kirk karate chop.

17:01.925 --> 17:02.891
I'm not even sure

17:02.893 --> 17:04.992
he knows I did it.

17:04.994 --> 17:06.694
Hey, Sheldon,

17:06.696 --> 17:09.030
I've got someone here who
might make you feel better.

17:09.031 --> 17:10.832
Hello, Sheldon.

17:10.834 --> 17:12.534
Professor Hawking!

17:12.536 --> 17:13.835
HAWKING:
I understand

17:13.837 --> 17:16.538
you're struggling
with professional jealousy.

17:16.540 --> 17:19.708
Thanks, Leonard, now he's
not gonna think I'm cool.

17:20.777 --> 17:23.878
Don't worry,
I know how you feel.

17:23.881 --> 17:26.348
I have never won a Nobel Prize.

17:26.349 --> 17:29.284
Oh, wow, that
doesn't seem fair.

17:29.286 --> 17:30.252
It's fine.

17:30.254 --> 17:32.220
I've been on <i>The Simpsons.</i>

17:34.191 --> 17:36.958
How do you deal with
the success of your colleagues?

17:36.960 --> 17:38.326
I remind myself

17:38.328 --> 17:41.529
every scientific advancement
is a victory.

17:41.531 --> 17:45.100
Also, I was on <i>Star Trek.</i>

17:46.536 --> 17:49.471
Oh, it was a good one. He played
poker with Sir Isaac...

17:49.473 --> 17:51.940
You don't care.

17:51.942 --> 17:53.942
Don't waste your time
on jealousy,

17:53.944 --> 17:56.511
Sheldon, you're too brilliant.

17:56.513 --> 17:58.613
How can you feel bad

17:58.615 --> 18:00.916
if Stephen Hawking says
you're brilliant?

18:00.918 --> 18:02.617
I can't.

18:02.619 --> 18:04.619
Thank you, Professor Hawking.

18:04.621 --> 18:06.221
You are a gift to mankind.

18:06.223 --> 18:09.157
There should be statues
of you everywhere.

18:09.159 --> 18:11.226
You know, the Lincoln Memorial
has a big chair.

18:11.228 --> 18:13.061
We could swap you right in.

18:15.332 --> 18:19.301
I always thought a motorized toy
of me would be cool.

18:22.606 --> 18:24.673
What a wonderful idea!

18:24.675 --> 18:27.142
How does this man
not have a Nobel?

18:27.144 --> 18:29.144
Do not tell Wolowitz.
Way ahead of you.

18:37.750 --> 18:39.984
A new study came out,
and it said that laughing

18:39.986 --> 18:42.420
makes your brain work better.

18:42.422 --> 18:44.221
And I know that's true
because laughing

18:44.223 --> 18:46.357
has made me the "smartiest."

18:46.359 --> 18:47.792
(laughter)

18:47.794 --> 18:49.093
Although, on the other hand,

18:49.095 --> 18:50.895
babies laugh a lot,
and they're dumb.

18:50.897 --> 18:52.363
(laughter)

18:52.365 --> 18:54.198
Do people know about her?

18:54.200 --> 18:55.700
'Cause she's delightful.

